      {
        "id": 2317477,
        "name": "Barry Rothof",
        "username": "Barry_Rothof",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/barry_rothof/{size}/1215_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-15T19:07:50.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Krug Champagne Brut Grande Cuv\u00e9e</strong><br>\n160 edition, fresh, rich and tangy flavours with ripe dried fruit and cream, subtle and elegant with fine bubbles.<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2014 Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Ganevat C\u00f4tes du Jura Les Grands Teppes Vieilles Vignes</strong><br>\nOozing up citrus, white fruits and chalky minerals. On the palate tight and focused with lemon and lime, purity and racy acidity. Youthful and quite powerful with good length.<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>2014 Cecile Tremblay Nuits St. Georges 1er Cru Aux Murgers</strong><br>\nSuperb aromas of ripe red fruit and black fruit. Great character with intense concentration but still very elegant with fabulous, complex and savoury undertones.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
