      {
        "id": 2317735,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-12-16T01:47:49.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Howard Cooper\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Howard Cooper:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don\u2019t remember the Murgers the two times I visited Trembley. Is this new to her, or did I just not taste (or at my age, remember) this wine?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>2009 was the first vintage of Murgers chez Tremblay. C\u00e9cile took it over earlier but decided to replant with superior vine material, so the vines are comparatively young. But the 2009 is drinking very well, and each vintage seems to gain in depth and energy. She makes an elegant rendition of Murgers with very gentle extraction and very careful pressing using a vertical press to avoid excessively firm tannins.</p>",
